messages.content:
You can configure IP-based access control in AWS API Gateway using an IAM policy, which you can attach to the API Gateway resource or method. Here's how to configure IP-based access control in AWS API Gateway:

1. Create a new IAM policy that restricts access to the specified IP addresses. 

a. Navigate to the IAM console.
b. Click on "Policies" and click on "Create policy."
c. Choose "Create Your Own Policy."
d. Give the policy a name and a description that relates to your IP-based access control use-case.
e. In the "Policy Document" section, enter the following code:

{
    "Version": "2012-10-17",
    "Statement": [
        {
            "Effect": "Deny",
            "Resource": "arn:aws:apigateway:{region}::/*/*",
            "Condition": {
                "NotIpAddress": {
                    "aws:SourceIp": ["192.0.2.0/24", "203.0.113.0/24"] 
                }
            }
        }
    ]
}

Note that you should replace {region} with your region, and the IP addresses in the "aws:SourceIp" field with your desired IP addresses and IP ranges.

2. Attach the IAM policy to your API Gateway resource or method.

a. Navigate to your API Gateway resource or method in the API Gateway console.
b. Click on "Method Request" or "Resource Policy" and then click on "Edit" to add an IAM policy.
c. Choose "AWS_IAM" as your authorization type.
d. In the "Authorizer" field, select "Custom IAM" and choose the IAM policy you just created.
e. Save the changes.

With the IAM policy attached to your API Gateway resource or method, only the specified IP addresses will be able to access your API. All other requests will be denied access.
